<seg id=1> US Open Tennis Tournament Enters Third Day </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, September 1. According to the reports by foreign news agencies, the US Open Tennis Tournament entered into its third day on August 31st.  The former champion, Sampras, who had been distressed by pain in his left ankle for over a month, competed in the tournament after his recovery from injuries and easily beat his opponent 3:0, entering the second round of male single. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> US player Sampras, the No. 1 in the world Tennis circle, hadn't appeared in contests since mid-July, was in good condition after the cure, and he defeated the opponent easily with the same score of 6:2 in half an hour in three run,  entering the second run . </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The eighth seed player, Ann Midwedev from Ukraine, defeated his opponent with 6:3, 6:4, 6:0, and entered into the second round. </seg>
<seg id=5> In fact, he can view this as a gift to celebrate his 20th birthday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> In the women's competition, seed 2, Sanchez from Spain, encounter challenge from French opponent Na Taugia, while eventually, Sanchez won and entered the third round by 6:2, 7:6. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The fifth seed, Japanese Kogo Date, Mar Fernandez from the US (seed 9), and the Champion in 1990 Sabatini from Argentina, all successfully entered into the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> According to another latest news, the United States contestant Michael Chang won in the second round of the male contest with 4:6, 6:2, 6:3, 7:6, and entered the third round. </seg>
</p>
